  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Post-traumatic seizures can appear frequently after a severe traumatic brain injury. Two
      types of seizures are usually identified: early seizures during the week following the trauma
      and late epilepsy afterward. Several antiepileptic drugs are usually used to prevent early
      seizures but no treatment has demonstrated any preventive effect against late epilepsy.
      Levetiracetam is an antiepileptic drug usually used for the treatment of epileptic patients
      and has pharmacologic properties that could also be interesting for the prevention of
      post-traumatic epilepsy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
